  "text": "To confirm data obtained in the whole-cell recording configuration and ascertain that AVP acts on the EPSP specifically, we applied it in the presence of the GABA A antagonist SR 95531 (5 mM) [CITATION_1] . In 14 slices in which a significant LTP was established after HFS, we observed a transient reduction of the fEPSP amplitude ( Fig. 3C ; S1 : 214.762.3% n = 14 and S2 : 212.162.2% n = 14, p,0.01 when comparing the fEPSPs amplitude for 1 min during the AVP application, at peak of the response 3 min latter and after returning to control values 15 min after AVP application), similar to that observed in control conditions. In slices in which HFS did not induce a LTP (n = 7), AVP had no effect on the fEPSP in the presence of SR 95531 (Fig. 3C) .",
